1 2. “High dosage tutoring” means in-person, subject-specific
2 tutoring conducted by an individual employed by or contracted with a
3 school district participating in the Oklahoma High Dosage Tutoring
4 Program after school hours for a minimum of three one-hour sessions
5 per week per cohort. Tutoring shall be conducted during a minimum
6 of ten (10) weeks in the fall semester and a minimum of twelve (12)
7 weeks in the spring semester.
8 C. 1. Participating school districts shall assess kindergarten
9 through third grade students participating in high dosage ELA
10 tutoring using the screening instrument required by Section
11 1210.508C of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes to track ELA academic
12 growth. Fourth- through eighth-grade students participating in high
13 dosage ELA tutoring shall be assessed using an assessment chosen by
14 the district to determine academic readiness for the next grade
15 level.
16 2. Participating school districts shall assess students
17 participating in high dosage mathematics tutoring using an
18 assessment chosen by the district to determine academic readiness
19 for the next grade level.
20 3. Results of screening instruments and assessments
21 administered pursuant to this subsection shall be electronically
22 reported to the State Department of Education three times a year at
23 intervals determined by the Department.
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 245 Page 2

1 D. The State Department of Education shall give priority for
2 participation in the Oklahoma High Dosage Tutoring Program to school
3 districts federally designated for additional targeted support and
4 improvement or comprehensive support and improvement under the
5 Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1965 as reauthorized by
6 P.L. No. 114-95, also known as the Every Student Succeeds Act.
7 Participation in the program shall be approved on a first-come,
8 first-served basis without any limitation other than the amount of
9 funds available for the program and the number of school districts
10 that apply.
11 E. High dosage tutors employed by or contracted with public
12 school districts participating in the Oklahoma High Dosage Tutoring
13 Program shall be awarded bonuses in the following amounts:
14 1. One Thousand Six Hundred Dollars ($1,600.00) for each cohort
15 educated by a high dosage tutor per semester; and
16 2. One Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00) for each academic grade
17 level increase in ELA or mathematics that each student within a
18 cohort experiences within one academic year.
19 F. 1. If the students in a high dosage tutor’s cohort do not
20 improve by at least half a grade level in their tutored subject
21 within the first year of the program, the tutor shall be placed on a
22 conditional one-year term of participation.
23 2. If the students in a high dosage tutor’s cohort fail to
24 achieve half a grade level of growth during the one-year conditional
ENGR. S. B. NO. 245 Page 3

1 term of participation, he or she shall lose eligibility to
2 participate in the program. A tutor who loses eligibility pursuant
3 to this paragraph may be reconsidered as a high dosage tutor after
4 two years.
5 3. If the students in a high dosage tutor’s cohort achieve half
6 a grade level of growth during the one-year conditional term of
7 participation, the tutor’s conditional status shall be lifted.
8 G. High dosage tutors shall be provided the necessary
9 information for each student’s subject-specific academic performance
10 level, as determined by the student’s current teacher of the tutored
11 subject.
12 H. 1. School districts participating in the Oklahoma High
13 Dosage Tutoring Program shall obtain written consent from a
14 student’s parent or legal guardian prior to allowing the student to
15 participate in high dosage tutoring.
16 2. If a student participating in high dosage tutoring fails to
17 attend a tutoring session, the tutor shall notify the student’s
18 school district, and the school district shall notify the student’s
19 parent or legal guardian.
20 3. If the parent or legal guardian of a student participating
21 in high dosage tutoring no longer wishes for the student to
22 participate, a student fails to attend nine high dosage tutoring
23 sessions during a semester, or a student’s behavior during tutoring
24 sessions requires disciplinary action, the student may be removed
