1 from the cohort. The performance of a student subject to the
2 provisions of this paragraph shall not count against the high dosage
3 tutor.
4 I. The State Board of Education shall promulgate rules to
5 implement the provisions of this section.
6 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
7 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-180.1 of Title 70, unless
8 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
9 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
10 for the State Department of Education to be designated the “High
11 Dosage Tutoring Revolving Fund”. The fund shall be a continuing
12 fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of
13 all monies received by the State Department of Education from gifts,
14 grants, donations, bequests, federal funds provided for the purpose
15 of funding high dosage tutoring, or state appropriations provided
16 for the purpose of implementing the provisions of Section 1 of this
17 act. All monies accruing to the credit of the fund are hereby
18 appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the State
19 Department of Education for the purpose provided for in this
20 section. Expenditures from the fund shall be made upon warrants
21 issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by
22 law with the Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise
23 Services for approval and payment.
24 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
